    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>In Pre-Columbian Mexico, small T-shaped hachuelas or axes used as money or a unit of exchange in markets. In Africa, full size objects in the shape of an ax and used as currency.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
